ents. By enhancing blood flow to the brain, Nimodipine helps address the underlying vascular issues contributing to cognitive decline in VD. [Data: Entities (2098), Relationships (2382)]\n\n## Cholinesterase inhibitors for cognitive enhancement\n\nCholinesterase inhibitors such as Rivastigmine and Galantamine are used to treat cognitive impairment in VD patients. These medications work by increasing acetylcholine levels in the brain, thereby improving memory and learning. Their widespread use underscores their importance in managing cognitive symptoms associated with VD. [Data: Entities (2099, 2100), Relationships (2384, 2386)]\n\n## Brain metabolism enhancers for cognitive function\n\nBrain metabolism enhancers like Piracetam, Pyritinol, and Citicoline are used to improve cognitive function in VD patients. These compounds enhance brain metabolism, supporting memory and cognitive performance. Their inclusion in VD treatment plans highlights the diverse therapeutic strategies employed to manage the condition. [Data: Entities (2101, 2102, 2103), Relationships (2387, 2388, 2389)]", "# Neuropathology and Affective Disorders\n\nThe community is centered around Neuropathology, which is a key entity studying brain structural changes in conditions like Alzheimer's disease and Affective Disorders. The relationships between these entities highlight the focus on understanding mental and neurological disorders through neuropathological research.\n\n## Neuropathology as the central entity\n\nNeuropathology is the central entity in this community, with a high degree of connections, indicating its importance in studying brain structural changes. It is linked to both Alzheimer's disease and Affective Disorders, suggesting its broad relevance in understanding various neurological and mental health conditions. [Data: Entities (425), Relationships (507, 509)]\n\n## Affective Disorders' connection to Neuropathology\n\nAffective Disorders are studied within the field of Neuropathology t